(enablePrefetching, numRCQEntries).explanation: Prefetching enablement is a configuration setting while RCQ entries are hardware buffer sizes that are typically fixed at design time and independent of prefetching configuration;

(enablePrefetching, power).explanation: Enabling prefetching increases processor activity by generating additional memory requests and activating prefetch logic, which directly increases overall power consumption;

(enablePrefetching, power_pad).explanation: Prefetching configuration does not affect the physical pad structures or their associated power consumption as these are fixed hardware design elements;
